==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indeclinable
<hw>In`de*clin"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indeclinabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ind⟦eacute⟧clinable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Decline</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>
<def>Not declinable; not varied by inflective terminations; <as>as,
<ex>nihil</ex> (nothing), in Latin, is an <ex>indeclinable</ex>
noun</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An indeclinable
word.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indeclinably</ent>⟦br⟧
